---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import ImageText from '../../components/ImageText.astro';
import PhotoMarquee from '../../components/PhotoMarquee.astro';
import BookingCTA from '../../components/BookingCTA.astro';

const photos = [
	{ src: '/neurological-rehabilitation/slider-1.jpg', alt: 'Neurological rehabilitation in progress' },
	{ src: '/neurological-rehabilitation/slider-2.jpg', alt: 'Hands-on neurological therapy' },
	{ src: '/neurological-rehabilitation/slider-3.jpg', alt: 'Balance and gait rehabilitation' },
	{ src: '/neurological-rehabilitation/slider-4.jpg', alt: 'Neuro physio session at Balance' },
	{ src: '/neurological-rehabilitation/slider-5.jpg', alt: 'Resistance training in neurological rehab' },
];

const bookingUrl = 'https://go.mindbodyonline.com/book/widgets/appointments/view/8068777f5e/services';

const faqs = [
	{ q: 'What is the difference between neurological physiotherapy and regular physiotherapy?', a: 'Neurological physiotherapy focuses specifically on conditions affecting the brain, spinal cord, and nerves, and how these impact movement, balance, and function.' },
	{ q: 'Can you help with dizziness and balance problems?', a: 'Yes. We offer vestibular physiotherapy for dizziness, balance issues, and falls prevention.' },
	{ q: 'Do you see children?', a: 'Yes. We work with babies, children, and adolescents with neurological, developmental, and movement concerns.' },
	{ q: 'Is neurological rehabilitation only for recent injuries?', a: 'No. We support people at all stages, whether symptoms are recent or long term.' },
	{ q: 'Will I get exercises to do at home?', a: 'Yes. Your therapist will build a practical programme that fits your needs and day-to-day life.' },
];
---
<Layout
	title="Neurological Physiotherapy in South West London"
	description="Neurological physiotherapy in South West London: assessment, hands-on therapy, balance and gait rehabilitation, vestibular work and Vojta Therapy."
>
	<PageHero title="in South West London" highlight="Neurological Physiotherapy" breadcrumb="Neurological Physiotherapy" />

	<PhotoMarquee images={photos} heightPx={140} speedSeconds={45} />

	<div class="service-intro">
	<ImageText eyebrow="Our approach" heading="Clinical, evidence-led" highlight="neurological rehabilitation" image="/neurological-rehabilitation/clinic-session.jpg" imageAlt="Neuro consultation">
		<p>Neurological conditions can change how you move, function, and manage day-to-day life.</p>
		<p>At Balance, neurological physiotherapy is about more than managing symptoms. It's about understanding how your nervous system is affecting movement, balance, strength, and coordination, and what needs to change to help you function more independently and confidently.</p>
		<p>We take a clinical, evidence-led approach to every case. From your first session, we assess how you move, what is limiting you, and where the greatest opportunities for progress are, then build a plan around your goals, your daily life, and your starting point.</p>
		<p>Whether you are recovering from neurological injury, living with a long-term condition, or trying to maintain independence and confidence, we meet you where you are and guide you forward.</p>
		<p><a href={bookingUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary">Book Now</a></p>
	</ImageText>
	</div>

	<ImageText reverse altBg eyebrow="Symptoms" heading="When to consider" highlight="neurological physiotherapy" image="/neurological-rehabilitation/body-2.jpg" imageAlt="Neurological symptoms assessment">
		<p>Neurological physiotherapy can help if you're dealing with:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Difficulty with walking, standing, or moving safely</li>
			<li>Balance problems, dizziness, or falls</li>
			<li>Muscle weakness, stiffness, or changes in tone</li>
			<li>Reduced coordination or control</li>
			<li>Fatigue affecting day-to-day function</li>
			<li>Loss of confidence with movement after illness or injury</li>
			<li>Developmental, postural, or movement concerns in babies and children</li>
		</ul>
		<p>If movement feels harder, less reliable, or less efficient than it should, it's worth addressing early.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText eyebrow="Treatment" heading="How we" highlight="work" image="/neurological-rehabilitation/body-3.jpg" imageAlt="Neurological treatment session">
		<p>Everything we do is built around one principle: helping you move better and function more confidently.</p>
		<p>Your treatment may include:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Hands-on therapy to improve movement and reduce restriction</li>
			<li>Targeted exercise to build strength, control, and endurance</li>
			<li>Balance and gait rehabilitation</li>
			<li>Vestibular rehabilitation for dizziness and balance problems</li>
			<li>Bobath-based therapy or Vojta Therapy where appropriate</li>
			<li>Clear education and practical strategies to support independence at home and in daily life</li>
		</ul>
		<p>We don't take a one-size-fits-all approach. Your programme is built around your condition, your goals, and the level you are currently at.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText reverse altBg eyebrow="Outcomes" heading="How we measure" highlight="your progress" image="/neurological-rehabilitation/body-4.jpg" imageAlt="Tracking neurological rehab progress">
		<p>We don't guess.</p>
		<p>From your first session, we establish a clear baseline of how you move, function, and manage day to day. As you progress, we regularly reassess, looking at balance, walking, strength, control, fatigue, and what you are practically able to do in everyday life.</p>
		<p>This keeps your treatment focused and accountable.</p>
		<p>For you, that means:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Clear evidence that you're improving</li>
			<li>A plan that adapts as your needs change</li>
			<li>Confidence in your ability to move, function, and stay as independent as possible</li>
		</ul>
		<p><a href="/outcomes" class="section-link">Read More About Outcome Measures &rarr;</a></p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText eyebrow="Our patients" heading="Who we" highlight="help" image="/neurological-rehabilitation/basketball-wheelchair.jpg" imageAlt="Adaptive sport">
		<p>We work with people across a wide range of neurological and vestibular needs.</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Adults recovering from stroke, brain injury, or spinal cord injury</li>
			<li>People living with Parkinson's, Multiple Sclerosis, neuropathy, or other neurological conditions</li>
			<li>Individuals with dizziness, vestibular problems, or falls risk</li>
			<li>Babies, children, and adolescents with developmental or neurological concerns</li>
			<li>People wanting to maintain strength, confidence, and independence with a long-term condition</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Whatever your starting point, the goal is the same: better movement, better function, better outcomes.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText reverse altBg eyebrow="Our team" heading="Our clinical" highlight="team" image="/neurological-rehabilitation/body-6.jpg" imageAlt="Neurological rehab clinical team">
		<p>Our neurological physiotherapy team is made up of highly experienced clinicians with specialist areas of expertise. You'll be matched with the right practitioner for your needs, whether that's neurological rehabilitation, vestibular physiotherapy, Vojta Therapy, or longer-term support with strength, mobility, and independence.</p>
		<p><strong>Jonathan Zulueta</strong> is a Consultant Vestibular Physiotherapist with over 20 years of experience. He specialises in balance disorders, dizziness, and neck-related neurological conditions, with additional expertise in osteoporosis.</p>
		<p><a href="/meet-the-team" class="section-link">Read More About Jonathan &rarr;</a></p>
		<p><strong>Dr Jose Sanz Mengibar</strong> is a Consultant Neurological Physiotherapist and Vojta Therapist with over 20 years of experience. He brings PhD-level expertise in reflex locomotion and neurological rehabilitation.</p>
		<p><a href="/meet-the-team" class="section-link">Read More About Jose &rarr;</a></p>
		<p><strong>Maxine Baillie-Harland</strong> provides dedicated neurological physiotherapy for both adults and children. She is known for her compassionate, patient-centred approach to neurological rehabilitation.</p>
		<p><a href="/meet-the-team" class="section-link">Read More About Maxine &rarr;</a></p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText eyebrow="Fees" heading="Pricing and" highlight="insurance" image="/neurological-rehabilitation/wheelchair-basketball.jpg" imageAlt="Wheelchair basketball player in action on the court">
		<p>We offer a transparent fee structure that reflects our level of clinical expertise.</p>
		<p><a href="/pricing#neurological-rehabilitation" class="section-link">Pricing Information &rarr;</a></p>
	</ImageText>

	<section class="faq-section faq-section--alt">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="section-header"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2></div>
			<div class="faq-list">
				{faqs.map((item) => (
					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary>{item.q}</summary>
						<div class="answer">{item.a}</div>
					</details>
				))}
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<BookingCTA />
</Layout>
